The handoff container builder image,
public.ecr.aws/m5u3u5p2/handoff-container-builder

is just a pre-configured kaniko image as in this directory (config.json).

## Build the image

To build this image, do:

docker build -t handoff-container-builder .

Push the image to a public repository:
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECR/latest/public/getting-started-cli.html

## Create handoff-container-builder task

This command will create the handoff-container-builder task definition:
```
handoff -p . -s dev cloud task create/update -v template_file="./task.yml"
```

Note: The custom task.yml is for TaskRoleArn modification. (TODO: Modify role.yml in services/cloud/aws/cloudformation_templates to give privilege to push the image to the image registry (ECR))

## Build project image on kaniko

This command prepares the tar.gz for kaniko and upload to S3, under the project subfolder "bundles":
```
handoff container bundle -p <project_dir>
```

Then this command builds the project's docker image as handoff task. Kaniko executes as a Fargate task, and upload the image to the image registry:
```
handoff cloud container build -p <project_dir>
```